Commentary Text: Thakur to Kohli, out Kohli Run Out!! Yes-no! Direct-hit at the striker's end from Lalit Yadav and Kohli is a goner! DC are cock-a-hoop. Taps a length ball towards point with soft hands and both batters set off. Maxwell sends him back. Lalit Yadav swoops in from backward point and hits the bullseye with a side-arm throw. He had one stump to aim and he nailed it despite being slightly off-balance. Excellent stuff from Lalit. For the second time this season, Kohli has been run-out. Kohli run out (Lalit Yadav) 12(14) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Khaleel Ahmed to du Plessis, out Caught by Axar!! In the air ... and ... taken! Khaleel Ahmed strikes in his first over. 140kph, away-slanter from a short of length, du Plessis shimmies down the track and moves leg-side before wafting his blade at it. Sliced it over point, went much squarer than he anticipated. Axar moves to his right from deep point and takes a safe catch. The bowler probably saw the step out of his crease and shortened his length. RCB lose both their openers cheaply. du Plessis c Axar b Khaleel Ahmed 8(11) [4s-2]
